<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2059] SSTableDeletingReference only deletes data files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2059</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Ching-Cheng Chen reports on the mailing list:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In SSTableDeletingReference, it try this operation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;components.remove(Component.DATA);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;before&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;STable.delete(desc, components);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the components was reference to the components object which was created inside SSTable by&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this.components = Collections.unmodifiableSet(dataComponents);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As you can see, you can&apos;t try the remove operation on that components object.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
